@*
    AppLogo — Inline SVG logo that responds correctly to dark/light mode.

    Using an inline <svg> (rather than <img src="...">), CSS can reach the SVG
    internals.  The wordmark paths carry fill:currentColor; app.css sets:
        .app-logo           { color: #1A1A24; }          ← light mode
        .app-dark .app-logo { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.87); } ← dark mode
    Both rules rely on CSS color inheritance, which only works when the SVG is
    part of the DOM — not when it is loaded as an <img> resource.
*@

